added.title: Cartoon Feud
added.description: Control Freak forces the Titans and the Scooby Gang to compete on Family Feud.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star Part 1
added.description: The Justice League holds a talent competition to find a superhero worthy of joining the team.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star Part 2
added.description: The competition heats up and Robin tries everything to win.

added.title: The Petals
added.description: When Leslie's petals begin falling off he feels like his good looks are fading, Gumball and Darwin use everything they know about style and beauty to try and help him. The only problem is they know nothing about style or beauty. As Gumball and Darwin's methods become more extreme, Leslie questions whether he's prepared to make the ultimate sacrifice for beauty.

added.title: The Pest
added.description: When they find Anais training herself for a brutal showdown, Gumball and Darwin realize their sister is being pestered at school by an annoying kid, Billy. They try to teach her how to resolve the problem peacefully but Billy has other ideas.

added.title: The Password
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are shocked to discover that Anais is Dad's favourite child. Mom has forced Dad to install a password on the computer. The pop-up clue advises them that the password is the name of Dad's favorite child. After trying "Gumball" and "Darwin" unsuccessfully, they discover the answer is, in fact, "Anais". They are determined to become Dad's favorites by any means necessary, even if it means undermining each other, plotting against Anais or driving a wedge between mom and dad . . .

added.title: The Photo
added.description: It's school picture day and Gumball has until 3pm to take one good photo - or have his legacy ruined forever.

added.title: The Picnic
added.description: Gumball and Darwin barely survive a school picnic in the Forest of Doom

added.title: Gyranoid of the Future
added.description: Apple and Onion struggle to ride Gyranoid of the Future, the craziest roller coaster at the carnival.

added.title: Asian-American Pacific Islander Heritage Month - Drawn to Food
added.description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Asian-American, Pacific Islander Heritage Month, and recognizing awesome kids all over the country who are drawn to, food!
added.seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

added.title: Journey to Maize Mountain Part 1
added.description: When Vic & Val destroy Monte Macabre's corn supply, they travel with Sal to Corn Mountain to replace it. But in order to get the corn, they have to shrink to the size of ants, creating all kinds of problems!
added.tags: vic and val - see it first

added.title: Journey to Maize Mountain Part 2
added.description: When Victor and Valentino destroy Monte Macabre's corn supply, they journey to Maíz Mountain with Sal to replace it. But in order to get the corn, they must shrink down to the size of ants and embark on a mythical adventure that they'll never forget!
added.tags: vic and val - see it first

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 1
added.description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 2
added.description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: The Dark Room
added.description: After getting rejected by a photography club, Val tries to get a picture of the legendary Chupacabra in order to prove himself.

added.title: The Collector
added.description: When Vic accidentally loses one of Val's prized coins Val makes a deal with a mysterious antiques collector to replace it, but the deal has terrible consequences.

added.title: The Boy Who Cried Lechuza
added.description: After faking an injury to get out of work, Vic gains sympathy from everyone while unknowingly attracting attention from a dangerous mythical creature.

added.title: Boss For a Day
added.description: When Chata lets Vic be the boss of the taco stand for the day Vic decides to fire Val, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Cuddle Monster
added.description: After being told by Chata that they can't get a pet, Vic & Val adopt a wild lizard, unaware of its magical properties, and decide to keep it secret from Chata.

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val holds a grudge against Vic, unwittingly attracting an evil cadejo, a mythological wolf-like beast.

added.title: It Grows
added.description: As everyone celebrates Valentino for growing his first facial hair, a jealous Vic resorts to magical methods to grow a mustache and compete for attention.

added.title: A New Don
added.description: When Vic & Val discover that Don isn't really himself, it's up to them to use his kooky codex of conspiracies to save him.

added.title: Churro Kings
added.description: When Vic & Val start making good money from selling churros at the taco stand, their lust for stuff makes them do dirty tricks to take out their competition.

added.title: Sharing Is Caring
added.description: Courtney refuses to share her valuable collectors item toy with her classmates.

added.title: Ant We All Just Get Along
added.description: Owen and Beth try to save an ant hill that Courtney and Leshawna want to destroy.

added.title: Cone in 60 Seconds
added.description: After Owen gets ripped off at the ice cream truck, the kids unite to right that wrong.

added.title: The Bad Guy Busters
added.description: Izzy wants to play a superhero game and is willing to do whatever it takes to get the others to see it through.

added.title: That's a Wrap
added.description: Duncan goes on a mission to scare Courtney during a field trip to the museum.

added.title: Tiger Fail
added.description: Gwen refuses to be pressured into choosing an ice cream flavor that she does not want.

added.title: A Ninjustice to Harold
added.description: Harold's world is turned upside down when Beth becomes the class ninja.

added.title: Having the Timeout of Our Lives
added.description: Owen forms a special bond with Duncan after having loads of fun with him during their timeouts.

added.title: Hic Hic Hooray
added.description: Bridgette gets the hiccups and becomes desperate to get rid of them.

added.title: Bananas & Cheese
added.description: Duncan is determined to stop the musical duo Bananas & Cheese from coming to the daycare.

added.title: Steam is the Word
added.description: In the heart of Silicon Valley, Ben has to stop Victorian villain Steam Smythe from securing an epic power source sealed in a Tesla time capsule.

added.title: The Beast Inside
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Max make a return to Max's alma mater but this time it's no homecoming. Dr. Animo has made a scary transformation and found a way to release the very dangerous animal nature of humans, including Max's life-long friend!

added.title: All Wet
added.description: No one believes Ben when he insists that one of the other patrons waiting in line at the World of Wet Water Park is the nefarious Frightwig disguised as a common girl. So Ben must prove his case while protecting park goers from her master plan: to destroy the park with its own water pressure!

added.title: Villain Time
added.description: Ben must go alien to save the Hoover Dam from disaster, but when tough guy hero Tim Buktu swoops in to help, Ben must figure out if Tim is friend or foe.

added.title: Drive You Crazy
added.description: After the Rust Bucket breaks down at a Mobile Home Park, Ben discovers they've stumbled on to the last leg of the Cali 10 Hundred, an epic, off-road auto race where mad driver Le Grange has returned for revenge against those that disqualified him years ago.

added.title: Tomorrow Today
added.description: When Max drags the kids to see a defunct "House of the Future" built by his childhood idol, Ben discovers Steam Smythe is busy excavating the joint on the search for a powerful device that will allow him to create devastating weapons for his war on progress. Only Max's devotion to his childhood idol and Ben's faith in dreams can save tomorrow... today!

added.title: Tooth Trouble
added.description: Puppycorn loses his first tooth and Unikitty's excited for her little bro, now he​ ​gets a visit from​ ​the​ ​legendary Tooth Fairy!​ ​But when the Tooth Fairy is a no-show, Unikitty and her friends take on the mantle and responsibilities. But will they play too fast and loose with loose teeth and hit a raw nerve?

added.title: Hawkodile Sensei
added.description: On a routine mission, Hawkodile finds some defenseless chipmunks that imprint on him.​ ​The bird bodyguard takes it upon himself to become their Sensei teach the younglings his warrior ways, but Unikitty worries his training is too intense. Will Hawkodile's "all work, no play" lifestyle push the chipmunks too far?

added.title: Who Took Toast
added.description: When Toast disappears from Unikitty's party she leads a search to find him and expose the toast-napper.

added.title: Spoooooky Game
added.description: The gang's weekly board game night has been getting a little too competitive lately, so when Unikitty finds a spooky old board game that's clearly haunted, their desire to win gets turned upside down, but cursed or not, they'll be the first to the finish line!

added.title: Little Prince Puppycorn
added.description: Puppycorn finally realizes he's a prince, so he wants to be in charge of the kingdom for once! Despite their friends' concerns, Unikitty makes Puppycorn ruler but realizes absolute power in the hands of the pup is too much for him to handle and his ideas aren't exactly great. Can they remove him from power while keeping the kingdom from revolting?

added.title: Top of the Naughty List
added.description: It's Christmas Eve and Brock is excited for Santa to come and visit as he settles down for a bedtime story from Master Frown, Unikitty and gang burst in. They are there to stop Master Frown from ruining any more Christmases. Frown pleads innocent but Unikitty and the gang tell the stories of the past Christmases he has already ruined.  Will Frown prove his innocence or will he rocket to the top of the Naughty List?

added.title: A Cold Goodbye
added.description: Having learned Zane is not dead, Master Wu prepares to go after him, but Lloyd and the other ninja take matters into their own hands and defy their Master.

added.title: The Never-Realm
added.description: The ninja arrive in the Never-Realm where they quickly find themselves overwhelmed. Luckily, they are taken in by a tribe of Ice Fishers who tell them Zane has been imprisoned by the evil Ice Emperor.

added.title: Fire Maker
added.description: The Ice Emperor learns of the ninja's arrival and sends his Blizzard Samurai warriors to destroy them and the villagers who sheltered them.

added.title: An Unlikely Ally
added.description: Lloyd runs afoul of the Ice Emperor's Blizzard Samurai but is rescued by a strange wolf with whom an unlikely friendship develops.

added.title: Kelsey the Worthy
added.description: When Kelsey demolishes a wall at Craig's house, her father takes away her sword. So she enlists Craig and JP to help prove to her father that she's still worthy.

added.title: The End Was Here
added.description: Craig tries to figure out how an ancient war that decimated the Creek began in hopes of stopping history from repeating itself.

added.title: Sunday Clothes
added.description: JP dirties his last clean clothes and he must wear his Sunday best to the creek.

added.title: Escape from Family Dinner
added.description: There's a huge water balloon fight at the creek but Craig is stuck at home for a family dinner, unless he can escape.

added.title: Monster in the Garden
added.description: Craig is determined to catch the monster that has been wreaking havoc in Granddad's garden.

added.title: The Curse
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP run afoul of some no-good teenage witches and are cursed! Lousy teenagers!

added.title: Dog Decider
added.description: Unable to make tough decisions, Craig decides to put his choices in the hands of a dog named Fred.

added.title: Bring Out Your Beast
added.description: Craig wants to play a popular card game, so he decides to borrow Bernard's vintage and valuable cards.

added.title: Yuri and the Bear
added.description: Baby Ice Bear lives alone in the arctic and meets a mysterious man named Yuri. Together they help each other survive the cold environment.

added.title: El cuarto oscuro
added.description: Tras ser rechazado por un club de fotografía, Val intenta conseguir una foto del legendario Chupacabra para demostrar su valor.

added.title: El Coleccionista
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic pierde una de las preciadas monedas de Val, Val hace un trato con un misterioso coleccionista de antigüedades para reemplazarla, pero el trato tiene consecuencias terribles.

added.title: Victor y la Lechuza
added.description: Después de fingir una lesión para no tener que trabajar, Vic se gana la compasión de todos mientras que, sin saberlo, atrae la atención de una peligrosa criatura mítica.

added.title: Jefe por un dia
added.description: Cuando Chata deja que Vic sea el jefe del puesto de tacos por un día, él decide despedir a Val, lo que trae consecuencias desastrosas.

added.title: Nueva Mascota
added.description: Después de que Chata les dijera que no pueden tener una mascota, Vic y Val adoptan un lagarto salvaje, sin conocer sus propiedades mágicas, y deciden mantenerlo en secreto para que Chata no se entere.

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val le guarda rencor a Vic, lo cual atrae sin querer a un malvado cadejo, una bestia mitológica parecida a un lobo.

added.title: Crece
added.description: Mientras todo el mundo celebra a Valentino porque le creció su primer vello facial, Vic se pone celoso y recurre a métodos mágicos para dejarse crecer el bigote y competir por la atención.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo Parte 1
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo Parte 2
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.

added.title: Sale el Don
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val descubren que Don Jalapeño no es realmente él mismo, depende de ellos usar el alocado libro de conspiraciones de Don para salvarlo.

added.title: Carl
added.description: A pleasant weekend goes awry when a monster attacks.

added.title: Thank You for Watching the Show
added.description: When KO finds moments of his life slipping by, he begins to suspect something weird is going on.

added.title: Beach Episode
added.description: Surf's up on a wacky beach adventure when our heroes are challenged to the ultimate beach battle.

added.title: OK A.U.!
added.description: An evil warlock takes our heroes to a strange alternate universe.

added.title: Villains' Night In
added.description: While Boxman and Venomous are out, Fink is reluctantly babysat by Darrell and Shannon.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Second Greatest Team Edition Part 2
added.description: The competition heats up and the Titans must find a way to beat the Hive Five.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Second Greatest Team Edition Part 1
added.description: The Justice League holds another talent competition to find the second best superhero team in the world.

added.title: Elements Part 4: Cloudy
added.description: Before they can restore Ooo, Finn and Jake will have to escape exile in an endless sky.

added.title: Elements Part 5: Slime Central
added.description: Finn and Jake infiltrate the new Slime Kingdom and are drawn into a heated skate battle.

added.title: The Return of Party Horse
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to help their friend Party Horse get back together with his girlfriend.

added.title: Just Friends
added.description: Rigby and Eileen get called away to Don's black belt ceremony forcing Mordecai and Margaret to hang out alone.

added.title: Furniture & Meat
added.description: Big money problems send Finn and Jake to Wildberry Kingdom.

added.title: Ghost Fly
added.description: Jake and the tree house are haunted by a vengeful spectre.

added.title: Gamers Never Say Die
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to find a rare, golden video game patch.

added.title: Party Horse
added.description: The guys want to help Party Horse pass his U.S. history test.

added.title: Garage Door
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to fix the garage door.

added.title: Perfect Day
added.description: Ben thinks he's having 'the perfect day' only to realize he's been put in a dream world by Enoch and the Forever Knights who are after the Omnitrix. Ben's "dream world" soon becomes a nightmare world, with Ben forced to live out his ultimate terror...being stuck at school! But with Max and Gwen's help, he's able to vanquish his nightmare foes and re-enter the real world where he takes down  Enoch...only to reveal an even more powerful knight...The Forever King.

added.title: Uncle Melvins
added.description: Legendary rock band, the Melvins, team up with Uncle Grandpa to help a young girl who wants to win her school's talent show.

added.title: Big Fat Alien Wedding
added.description: Ben and Gwen accompany Max to a wedding, which doesn't make Ben particularly happy, especially given the fact he has to wear a tux and learn how to dance. During the wedding it's revealed that the bride's parents are aliens while the groom's family are ex-Plumbers. It turns out the bride's parents are out to sabotage the wedding because of a long lasting feud with the Plumbers, and take action by demonstrating their destructive powers and causing deadly havoc. Ben, Max and Gwen enter the fray and not only save the day, but make sure the ceremony goes on as planned.

added.title: The Bike Ride
added.description: Pizza Steve desperately tries to prevent the gang from finding out his shameful secret.

added.title: Hiccup Havok
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a kid who can't get rid of the hiccups.

added.title: The Little Mer-Tiger
added.description: The origin of Tiger is told as a flashback.  As the legend goes, Tiger used to be a mermaid.  One day the evil ruler of the sea, Bubble Grandpa, demanded a hamburger and picked Tiger to retrieve it.  He used his magic sea powers to give Tiger legs and send her ashore.  But Tiger grew to love the land, and with the help of her new friend, Uncle Grandpa, defeated the evil sea ruler and got to keep her legs.

added.title: Back to the Library
added.description: Uncle Grandpa uses time travel to convince his past self to return a library book on time.

added.title: Ghost Princess
added.description: Finn and Jake try to solve Ghost Princess' unsolved murder.

added.title: The Last Donnycorn
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn is hunted by a seemingly unstoppable foe, the Powerpuff Girls have to find a way to save him before it's too late!

added.title: Problemas Dentales
added.description: A Puppycorn se le cae su primer diente, y Unikitty está emocionada por su hermanito, ique ahora recibirá la visita de la legendaria Hada de los Dientes! Pero cuando el Hada de los Dientes no aparece, Unikitty y sus amigos asumen la responsabilidad. ¿Acaso se meterán demasiado rápido y con demasiada soltura con los dientes sueltos y tocarán un nervio sensible?

added.title: Splitsville
added.description: The girls learn to appreciate each others's style after having to each fight solo.

added.title: Bring Me the Spark of Optimus Prime Part 1
added.description: The Decepticons compete to be the first to bring Megatron Optimus Prime's spark while Hot Rod chases the "Moon Cheetah."

added.title: Bring Me the Spark of Optimus Prime Part 2
added.description: Slipstream searches for her missing Seekers while Hot Rod's "Moon Cheetah" chase brings him unexpectedly aboard the Nemesis.

added.title: Trials Part 1
added.description: Following the network of GroundBridges left by the Allspark, Optimus and Megatron finally discover the Allspark, and its Guardian, Cheetor.

added.title: Trials Part 2
added.description: Cheetor attempts to judge whether Optimus or Megatron are more worthy of the Allspark, but an unexpected visitor dashes all the bots' plans.

added.title: Dark Birth Part 1
added.description: While Starscream acquires new power through the Allspark, the Autobots mistakenly assume Starscream is still under Megatron's command.

added.title: Dark Birth Part 2
added.description: The Autobots and Decepticons battle aboard the Nemesis while Starscream uses the Allspark and Vector Sigma to create new allies.

added.title: Dr. Animo and the Mutant Ray
added.description: Dr. Animo has broken out of jail, and has been tracking down Ben, intent on revenge. At the same time, Ben's broken off a piece of the Omnitrix, and as a result, has turned into weird alien combinations, i.e. StinkArms.

added.title: Quien se llevo a Pan
added.description: Cuando Pan desaparece de la fiesta de Unikitty, ila princesa lidera una búsqueda para encontrarlo y desenmascarar al secuestrador de tostadas!

added.title: The Tails of Mardrynia
added.description: After reading a book about a mystical animal society in class, Clarence is inspired to round up local animals and recreate an animal world of his own to cheer up his friend Percy. But will Percy take the game too far?

added.title: Clarence Wendle and the Eye of Coogan
added.description: Clarence and other students find the crusty old journal of Coogan filled with clues leading to a mysterious treasure. Clarence spearheads the team of treasure hunters to journey through the perils of Aberdale seeking the lost Eye of Coogan.

added.title: Sneaky Peeky
added.description: After missing out on a chance to see the premiere of the new Robofrog movie trailer, the trio devises a plan to sneak into the theater and catch a glimpse before anyone else. However, when they accidentally damage the reel, they're forced to fix it or fess up!

added.title: Game Show
added.description: While shopping with his Mom, Clarence discovers Breehn hiding in a clothes rack. Under the guise of trying on new clothes for their moms, they sneak out to find a local gameshow being hosted inside the Aberdale Mall.

added.title: Plant Daddies
added.description: When Ms. Baker pairs up the kids to act as parents for a sprout, Sumo and Clarence learn all about good parenting. Jeff buys toys instead of fertilizer and Chelsea and Kimby get to know each other.

added.title: La Maldicion
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP entran en conflicto con unas brujas adolescentes deshonestas, ique les lanzan una maldición! iQué adolescentes malvadas!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Perro Decisivo
added.description: Incapaz de tomar decisiones difíciles, Craig decide poner sus decisiones en manos de un perro llamado Fred.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Saca tu Bestia
added.description: Craig quiere jugar a un popular juego de cartas, así que decide tomar prestadas las cartas antiguas y valiosas de Bernard.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Show de momias
added.description: Duncan sale en una misión para espantar a Courtney durante una excursión al museo.

added.title: Fallo de tigre
added.description: Gwen se niega a que la presionen para elegir un sabor de helado que no quiere.

added.title: Una ninja justicia para Harold
added.description: El mundo de Harold queda de cabeza cuando sus compañeros declaran que Beth es la verdadera ninja de la clase.

added.title: El castigo de mi vida
added.description: Owen forma un nexo especial con Duncan después de que ambos se divirtieran mucho durante sus castigos.

added.title: Frenemy
added.description: When the coolest girl in school befriends the girls, she charms them into becoming her accomplices in a series of adventurous crimes.

added.title: Arrested Development
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop the evil Robots from Dimension 12 while trapped in their own pre-pubescent bodies, thanks to Ben's childhood rival.  (Introducing Billy Billions.)

added.title: Hora De Ser Villano
added.description: Ben debe transformarse en alienígena para evitar un desastre en la represa Hoover, pero cuando Tim Buktu, el heroico tipo rudo, se precipita para ayudar, Ben debe descubrir si Tim es su amigo...o su enemigo.

added.title: Hip hip Hurra
added.description: Bridgette tiene hipo y está desesperada por librarse de ellos.

added.title: Once Upon a Townsville
added.description: When a dainty princess on a mission comes to Townsville, the girls must learn the superhero way isn't always the right way.

added.title: Conduciendo A La Locura
added.description: Cuando la Chatarra se rompe en un parque de casas rodantes, Ben descubre que se encuentran en la última etapa del Cali 10 Hundred-una carrera de autos épica todo terreno-en la que LaGrange, el piloto demente, ha regresado en busca de venganza contra aquellos que lo descalificaron hace años.

added.title: Ben Again
added.description: When Eon causes 11-year old Ben swap minds with teen Ben, it's up to Gwen, Rook, and Professor Paradox to set things straight.  (Featuring Eon and Professor Paradox.)

added.title: Manana Es Hoy
added.description: Cuando Max arrastra a los niños a ver una "Casa del futuro" obsoleta construida por su ídolo de la infancia, Ben descubre que Vapor Smythe está ocupado excavando el lugar en busca de un dispositivo poderoso que le permitirá crear armas devastadoras para su guerra en progreso. Solo la devoción de Max por su ídolo de la infancia y la fe de Ben en los sueños puede salvar el mañana...ihoy mismo!

added.title: Viral Spiral
added.description: When the Amoeba Boys wreak havoc on the internet, Bubbles has to hack her sisters in to stop them.

added.title: Store 23
added.description: While out looking for the elusive 23rd Mr. Smoothy's store with Blukic and Driba, Ben meets an alternate version of himself. (Guest-starring Aziz Ansari as Ben 23.)

added.title: Showdown Part I
added.description: The Faction infiltrates Galvan in an attempt to destroy Azmuth.  (Introducing new Nemetrix aliens Omnivoracious & Vicetopus.)

added.title: The Throw Down/Brawl for It All
added.description: The Throw Down: Lightning reveals his discovery of the Mind Core Cell but the AO arrive only to discover that Magnus has already beaten them to it./Brawl for It All: With both team's Bakugan knocked into a hibernation state by the Mind Core Cell only Dan and Magnus remain locked in a brawl for it all!

added.title: Career Opportunities/Punch the Clock
added.description: Career Opportunities: After defeating Magnus the AO get an offer of employment from a surprising source Philomena Dusk!/Punch the Clock: During a commercial to celebrate their joining the AAAnimus team Dan and the AO rebel before they sellout.

added.title: High Flying Hostiles/Backfire Brawl
added.description: High Flying Hostiles: While escorting the Mind Core Cell to AAAnimus Campus, the AO are attacked by Masato Kazami and his Body Guards./Backfire Brawl: Philomena's attempt to refocus the Mind Core Cell's power backfires and the AO must fight their fellow employees inside the AAAnimus Campus.

added.title: A Bot and His Dog
added.description: Tired of fielding of low stakes house calls, Mega Man gets what he wishes for when Hypno Woman hijacks the local power plant.

added.title: This Man, This Man Man!
added.description: When Guts Man goes on a ravenous rampage across the city, Mega Man must turn to an unlikely ally, Man Man, a bumbling DIY human analog to our hero.

added.title: A Guilded Cage
added.description: Mega Man must stop Namagem and an army of hypnotized Good Guild bots from breaking into Dr. Light's lab.

added.title: To Air Is Robot
added.description: Air Man stakes a claim on the skies above Silicon City, threatening anything that trespasses on his airspace.

added.title: Watt's Happening?!
added.description: When Elec Man derails the school play by hijacking Silicon Central's power, Aki/Mega Man must use what he has learned onstage to defeat his supercharged foe.

added.title: T.G.I.S
added.description: The Secret Saturdays come to Bellwood to investigate a rash of chupacabra attacks.

added.title: La Celula Nucleo
added.description: Los Fantásticos defienden la Célula Núcleo de un ataque de Tiko, y en el último intento de Dan por salvarla, él y Drago logran liberar un nuevo poder.

added.title: Hogar, dulce hogar
added.description: Los Fantásticos vuelven a casa y se dan cuenta de que el tiempo no ha pasado. Pronto descubren que su conocimiento acerca de las batallas ha aumentado de forma exponencial.

added.title: Un Aliado Peculiar
added.description: Lloyd se enfrenta a los Samurais Blizzard del Emperador de Hielo, pero es rescatado por un lobo extraño con quien desarrolla una amistad peculiar.

added.title: El Hacedor de Fuego
added.description: El Emperador de Hielo se entera de la llegada de los ninjas y envía a sus guerreros Samurais Blizzard a destruirlos, y a todos los aldeanos que los albergaron.

added.title: Framing Device/Bad Actors
added.description: Framing Device: When confronted by China Riot Lia learns to evolve Pegatrix after realizing the true meaning behind her filming obsession./Bad Actors: Dan tries to lie about evolving Drago and gets exposed while the team face off against Duran Dane and his unhappy Bakugan Nillious.

added.title: Tripped Up/Power Tripp
added.description: Tripped Up: Dan and Wynton stumble on both a possible hidden location of the Mind Core Cell and Colonel Tripp who wants the energy source for himself./Power Tripp: After a falling out with Dan, Wynton is mind-controlled by Tripp who stages an attack to ignite a war between Brawlers and the Military.

added.title: A Real Steal/Lightning Unleashed
added.description: A Real Steal: Dan embarks on a solo adventure to outdo Magnus's new team of Bakugan Brawlers and winds up having to be saved by them instead./Lightning Unleashed: Lightning uncovers the Mind Core Cell buried beneath the Earth and battles Stata the Hunter in an effort to protect its secret.

added.title: Lightfall Part 2
added.description: Lord Obsidian attacks the Lighthouse, but Mega Man overcomes his insecurity and works with his family to repel the big bad, who's rescued at the last second by a mysterious lieutenant, Namagem.

added.title: Rush to Greatness
added.description: Rush puts his new battle upgrades to the test in a battle with Wave Man.

added.title: Swish
added.description: Namagem attacks Mega Man using a variety of powers, revealing that they both can replicate schematics. However, Namagem can carry more than three at a time! The true beginning of the mysterious villain's arc begins here.

added.title: Minus Mini
added.description: When Mega Mini is kidnapped by Blasto Woman, Mega Man must track down his missing partner without the full use of his own systems.

added.title: A Cut Above
added.description: Aki and Bert accidentally damage a bonsai tree outside the Lighthouse, sending the Lights' perfectionist gardener on a slicing-and-dicing spree as Cut Man.

added.title: Silent Strike Part 1
added.description: Optimus and the Autobots infiltrate Decepticon Territory to destroy the Dark Matrix Megatron stole from a mysterious bot known only as "The Other One."

added.title: Silent Strike Part 2
added.description: Megatron tries desperately to prevent The Other One from entering their universe.

added.title: The Other One Part 1
added.description: The Other One and his Super Soldiers arrive, forcing Optimus and Megatron to fight together.

added.title: The Other One Part 2
added.description: The Other One reveals himself as an all-powerful Megatron from a universe where Optimus Prime is no more.

added.title: Sea of Tranquility Part 1
added.description: Optimus Prime and the Autobots battle Megatron and the Deceptions on Earth's Moon.

added.title: Sea of Tranquility Part 2
added.description: The Autobots struggle to stop the Decepticon's planet-cracking weapon as it targets Earth.

added.title: Bad Moon Rising Part 1
added.description: Starscream makes a play for leadership of the Deceptions as the Autobots storm the Decepticon's Moon Base.

added.title: Bad Moon Rising Part 2
added.description: The Autobots work to stop the Moon from crashing into the Earth as Starscream must reckon with betraying Megatron.

added.title: The Visitor Part 1
added.description: Bumblebee searches for any information his fellow Autobots might have regarding a strange creature he saw on the Moon.

added.title: The Visitor Part 2
added.description: Dino-Mode Grimlock careens out-of-control around the Ark after drinking Wheeljack's hyper-fuel.

added.title: Sensei Halcondrilo
added.description: En una misión de rutina, Halcondrilo encuentra algunas ardillas indefensas que lo siguen como abrojos. El ave guardaespaldas decide convertirse en Sensei para enseñar a los jóvenes sus destrezas de guerrero. Pero Unikitty teme que su entrenamiento sea demasiado intenso. ¿El estilo de vida de Halcondrilo en el que todo es trabajo y no hay tiempo para el juego hará que las ardillitas sobrepasen sus límites?

added.title: Juego tenebroso
added.description: Últimamente, la noche semanal de juegos de mesa de la banda se volvió demasiado competitiva, así que cuando Unikitty encuentra un viejo y espeluznante juego de mesa que claramente está embrujado, los deseos de ganar del grupo quedan dados vuelta, pero con o sin embrujo, iquieren ser los primeros en cruzar la línea de llegada!

added.title: Ropa Dominguera
added.description: JP ensucia su última ropa limpia y debe ponerse su mejor ropa de domingo para ir al arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Compartir es querer
added.description: Courtney se niega a compartir su valioso juguete de coleccionista con sus amigos.

added.title: Escape de la Cena Familiar
added.description: En el arroyo se disputa una enorme pelea con globos acuáticos, pero Craig está atrapado en la cena familiar, a menos que pueda escapar.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Y todos nos llevamos bien
added.description: Owen y Beth tratan de salvar un hormiguero que Courtney y Leshawna quieren destruir.

added.title: Monstruo en el Jardin
added.description: Craig está decidido a atrapar al monstruo que ha estado desatando un caos en el jardín del abuelo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Helado en 60 segundos
added.description: Después de que a Owen lo engañan en un camión de helados, los niños se unen para solucionarlo.

added.title: Los Caza Chicos Malos
added.description: Izzqy quiere jugar un juego de superhéroes y está dispuesta a hacer lo que sea por ello.

added.title: Principito perricornio
added.description: Puppycorn por fin se da cuenta de que es un príncipe, iy quiere estar a cargo del reino por una vez! A pesar de las preocupaciones de sus amigos, Unikitty permite que Puppycorn sea el rey, pero pronto, el poder absoluto en las manos del cachorro se le hace difícil de manejar, y sus ideas no son lo que se diría muy geniales. ¿Podrán removerlo del poder mientras evitan un levantamiento del pueblo?

added.title: Vapor Es La Palabra
added.description: En el corazón de Silicon Valley, Ben debe impedir que Vapor Smythe, el villano victoriano, consiga una fuente de poder épica sellada en una cápsula del tiempo diseñada por Tesla.

added.title: Una Fria Despedida
added.description: Habiendo aprendido que Zane no está muerto, el Maestro Wu se prepara para ir tras él, pero Lloyd y el otro ninja toman el asunto en sus propias manos y desafían a su Maestro.

added.title: La Bestia Interior
added.description: Ben, Gwen y Max regresan a la universidad de Max, pero esta vez no les dan una cálida bienvenida. El Doctor Ánimo ha hecho una transformación escalofriante y ha descubierto un modo de liberar la peligrosa naturaleza animal de los seres humanos...iincluida la del amigo de toda la vida de Max!

added.title: Todo Mojado
added.description: Nadie le cree a Ben cuando insiste en que uno de los demás clientes que aguarda en la fila del parque acuático es la malvada Frightwig disfrazada de niña común. Por eso, Ben debe demostrar que dice la verdad mientras protege a los asistentes al parque del plan maestro de la villana: idestruir el parque con su propia presión acuática!

added.title: El Reino del Jamas
added.description: Los ninja llegan al Never-Realm donde rápidamente se sienten abrumados. Afortunadamente, son recibidos por una tribu de pescadores de hielo que les dicen que Zane ha sido encarcelado por el malvado Emperador de hielo.

added.title: Bananas y Queso
added.description: Duncan está decidido a evitar que el dúo Banana y Queso se presente en la guardería.

added.title: Aventura en el laberinto
added.description: Perdidos en el laberinto de Vestroia, Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a poderosas fuerzas que parecen luchar por el control del planeta.

added.title: Atrapados en la jungla
added.description: Aún perdidos en Vestroia, Los Fantásticos experimentan los efectos de la Célula Núcleo que altera sus cuerpos, y se encuentran cara a cara con el monstruo Bakugan, Tiko.

added.title: Demonios internos
added.description: Los Fantásticos encuentran la forma de salir de Vestroia, pero descubren que en realidad están en un mundo paralelo.

added.title: Gyranoide del Futuro
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín se esfuerzan por subir a la montaña rusa más loca del parque de diversiones.

removed.title: Pruebas de Diversion
removed.description: Manzana y Cebollín quieren convertirse en la "Gente más divertida" de esta semana.

removed.title: Fun Proof
removed.description: Apple and Onion want to become this week's "Most Fun People".
